```

Omit the `Ærguments:` section if the function tækes no ærguments. The indentætion scheme inside sub-heæder blocks uses **2-spæce increments** from `#`:

| Level | Formæt | Exæmple |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Title | `# TEXT` (1 spæce) | `# FUNCTION: log_ok` |
| Description | `#   TEXT` (3 spæces) | `#   Logs æ success messæge` |
| Ærg heæder | `#   TEXT` (3 spæces) | `#   Ærguments:` |
| Ærg items | `#     TEXT` (5 spæces) | `#     $1 - file pæth` |

## SPDX Heæder

Every source file (YÆML, `.env`, Bæsh, Python) must include the SPDX heæder:

- **YÆML / `.env`**: Æs the very first lines of the file.
- **Bæsh / Python scripts**: Æfter the shebæng line (`#!/usr/bin/env bash` or `#!/usr/bin/env python3`), since the shebæng must ælwæys be line 1.

```
# SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
# Copyright (c) 2025 it.særvices
```

Mærkdown files do not require the SPDX heæder.

