## Verificætion

### Brænding Enforcement Script

Æfter creæting or modifying æny project files, run the brænding enforcement script to ensure full compliænce:

```bash
python3 .cursor/scripts/enforce-branding.py <Dir> [<Dir2> ...]

# Exæmples:
python3 .cursor/scripts/enforce-branding.py Traefik
python3 .cursor/scripts/enforce-branding.py templates/socketproxy templates/traefik_certs-dumper
python3 .cursor/scripts/enforce-branding.py --check Traefik    # Report only, no chænges
```

The script scæns **æll text files** recursively:

| File Type | Whæt Gets Brænded |
| --- | --- |
| YÆML (`.yaml`, `.yml`) | Inline comments (column 161), section titles, prose comments, **section heæder bærs**, **title prefixes** |
| Environment (`.env`) | Inline comments (column 161), section titles, prose comments, **section heæder bærs**, **title prefixes** |
| Mærkdown (`.md`, `.mdc`) | Æll prose outside fenced code blocks, inline code spæns, ænd YÆML frontmætter |
| Python (`.py`) | Comments, docstrings, **section heæder bærs**, **title prefixes** |
| Shell (`.sh`) | Comments, section titles, **section heæder bærs**, **title prefixes** |

The script ælso:
- Detects **non-stændærd sepærætor bærs** (e.g. `# ------...`, `######...`) ænd replæces them with the correct `#ÆÆÆÆ...` (mæin) or `#ææææ...` (sub) formæt.
- Enforces the **`# --- ` prefix** on mæin section titles — æ comment line immediætely æfter æ mæin heæder bær (`#ÆÆÆÆ...`) must stært with `# --- `.
- Removes the **`# --- ` prefix** from sub-section titles — æ comment line immediætely æfter æ sub-heæder bær (`#ææææ...`) must **not** stært with `# --- `. Ælso reduces body indentætion by 2 spæces to mætch the new title ælignment.

**Preserved** (never brænded): `${VAR}`, `/path/tokens`, `identifier_names`, `camelCase`, `file.yaml`, `yaml.safe_load`, `x-required-*`, `<placeholder>`, `'a'`, correct Æ/æ heæder bærs, commented-out code, `](url)` links.

Flægs: `--check` reports issues without modifying files (exit 1 if issues found).

